d  control plane for Kubernetes clusters. It enables seamless workload deployment, scaling, and management across on-premises and multi-cloud  setups, addressing operational challenges, reducing vendor lock-in, and enhancing disaster recovery and infrastructure efficiency.","integrations":"Volcano, Kubeflow, Kyverno, Pytorch, TensorFlow, Flink, Spark, OpenKruise, Grafana, Prometheus, Argo, Flux, Istio, Filebeat, Submariner, Velero, etc.","personas":["Cloud Architects","Platform Engineers","DevOps Engineer","DevOps practitioners","DevSecOps practitioners"],"release_rate":"Every 3 months","tags":["multi-cloud","hybrid cloud"],"use_case":"Karmada (Kubernetes Armada) is a Kubernetes management system that enables you to run your cloud-native applications across multiple Kubernetes clusters and clouds, with no changes to your applications. By speaking Kubernetes-native APIs and providing advanced scheduling  capabilities, Karmada enables truly open, multi-cloud Kubernetes. Karmada aims to provide turnkey automation for multi-cluster application management in multi-cloud and hybrid cloud scenarios, with key  features such as centralized multi-cloud management, high availability, failure recovery, and traffic scheduling."},"tag":["runtime"],"twitter_url":"https://x.com/karmada_io"},{"category":"Orchestration & Management","homepage_url":"https://keda.sh/","id":"orchestration-management--scheduling-orchestration--keda","logo":"logos/c87a77d52e0b19e58b98012864dbd5d963a4c4d97c767b15e074d30077104b12.svg","name":"KEDA","subcategory":"Scheduling & Orchestration","website":"https://keda.sh/","accepted_at":"2020-03-12","additional_categories":[{"category":"Serverless","subcategory":"Installable Platform"},{"category":"AI Native Infra","subcategory":"Orchestration and Scheduling"}],"artwork_url":"https://github.com/cncf/artwork/blob/master/examples/graduated.md#keda-logos","audits":[{"date":"2023-02-02","type":"security","url":"https://github.com/trailofbits/publications/blob/master/reviews/2023-01-keda-securityreview.pdf","vendor":"Trail of Bits"}],"blog_url":"https://keda.sh/blog","clomonitor_name":"keda","crunchbase_url":"https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/cloud-native-computing-foundation","devstats_url":"https://keda.devstats.cncf.io/","featured":{"label":"CNCF Graduated","order":1},"graduated_at":"2023-08-22","incubating_at":"2021-08-18","lfx_slug":"KEDA","maturity":"graduated","repositories":[{"url":"https://github.com/kedacore/keda","primary":true}],"slack_url":"https://kubernetes.slack.com/archives/CKZJ36A5D","summary":{"release_rate":"Every 4 months"},"tag":["runtime"],"twitter_url":"https://twitter.com/kedaorg","youtube_url":"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLvjRi5R9GQfASIcL4MLTfg2ZOoBdIi5Kq"},{"category":"Orchestration & Management","homepage_url":"https://knative.dev","id":"orchestration-management--scheduling-orchestration--knative","logo":"logos/6a1b7572490f95cada1836b3e0f932e5ff10c683bc1167b08ff868fb7867cfd5.svg","name":"Knative","subcategory":"Scheduling & Orchestration","website":"https://knative.dev","accepted_at":"2022-03-02","additional_categories":[{"category":"Serverless","subcategory":"Installable Platform"},{"category":"Wasm","subcategory":"Embedded Functions"},{"category":"AI Native Infra","subcategory":"Orchestration and Scheduling"}],"artwork_url":"https://github.com/knative/docs/tree/main/docs/images/logo","audits":[{"date":"2023-07-13","type":"fuzzing","url":"https://github.com/knative/docs/tree/main/reports/ADA-knative-fuzzing-audit-22-23.pdf","vendor":"Ada Logics"},{"date":"2023-11-27","type":"security","url":"https://github.com/knative/docs/blob/main/reports/ADA-knative-security-audit-2023.pdf","vendor":"Ada Logics"}],"clomonitor_name":"knative","crunchbase_url":"https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/cloud-native-computing-foundation","description":"Knative is a developer-focused serverless application layer which is a great complement to the existing Kubernetes application constructs. Knative consists of three components: an HTTP-triggered autoscaling container runtime called “Knative Serving”, a CloudEvents-over-HTTP asynchronous routing layer called “Knative Eventing”, and a developer-focused function framework which leverages the Serving and Eventing components, called \"Knative Functions\".","devstats_url":"https://knative.devstats.cncf.io/","featured":{"label":"CNCF Graduated","order":1},"graduated_at":"2025-09-11","incubating_at":"2022-03-02","lfx_slug":"knative","mailing_list_url":"https://groups.google.com/d/forum/knative-users","maturity":"graduated","repositories":[{"url":"https://github.com/knative/serving","primary":true}],"slack_url":"https://slack.cncf.io","stack_overflow_url":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/knative","summary":{"business_use_case":"The power of Knative’s eventing and serverless features allows companies to bridge processes between external eventing systems with services and functions in Kubernetes.","integrations":"Apache Kafka, RabbitMQ, Redis, CNCF Buildpacks, Docker, Podman","intro_url":"https://knative.dev/docs/getting-started/","personas":["Cloud Architects","Cloud Developers","Platform Engineers","DevOps Engineers","DevOps Practitioners"],"release_rate":"Quarterly major releases","tags":["Serverless","CloudEvents","Functions","Scaling","Applications"],"use_case":"Knative is system that helps teams develop, build, manage, and maintain processes in Kubernetes. Its purpose is to simplify, automate, and monitor deployments of Kubernetes so teams spend less time on maintenance and more time on app development and projects. Knative takes over repetitive and time-intensive tasks while removing obstacles and delays."},"tag":["runtime"],"twitter_url":"https://twitter.com/KnativeProject","youtube_url":"https://www.youtube.com/c/KnativeProject"},{"category":"Orchestration & Management","homepage_url":"https://koordinator.sh","id":"orchestration-management--scheduling-orchestration--koordinator","logo":"logos/e87455bdd8e